            <h1 class="display-4 display-4 mb-3 inria-serif-regular">Understanding <br class="d-md-none"><span style="color:#ffc107;">Waste Management</span></h1>
            <p class="inria-serif-regular">Learn the fundamental concepts of waste management, including its importance, types of waste, and the environmental impacts of improper disposal. This page provides essential knowledge needed to better understand waste-related issues.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container container_waste">
      <div class="learn_card" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="800">
        <div class="row align-items-center g-5">
 
          <div class="col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="mb-4 inria-serif-regular"> What is<span class="inria-serif-light-italic" style="color: #c5a059;"> waste management? </span></h2>
           
            <p class="fw-bold mb-2" style="color: #c5a059;">Definition</p>
 
            <p class="mb-4"> Waste management is the process of collecting, sorting, transporting, recycling, treating, and disposing of waste in a safe and efficient way. It also includes monitoring waste to reduce pollution and protect the environment and public health.</p>
           
            <p class="fw-bold mb-2" style="color: #c5a059;">Importance of Proper Waste Disposal</p>
 
            <p>Proper waste disposal helps reduce environmental pollution, prevent health risks, conserve natural resources, and decrease the amount of waste sent to landfills. It also supports recycling and sustainable practices, creating cleaner and healthier communities for the future.</p>
 
          </div>
 
          <div class="col-lg-5 text-center">
            <img src="pbl_image/learn_workers.png" alt="Workers managing waste" class="learn_image img-fluid">
          </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
 
